</div>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1163165-i-just-began-this-book-and-certainly-do">I Just began this book and certainly do not have a degree in English although I enjoy it as a hobby. I have noticed that the author uses the word &quot;sweet&quot; a lot. Could someone please enllighten me as to what this means? Boy, do I feel dumb. Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1163165'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F955946.Brief_Interviews_with_Hideous_Men">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
