<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1163165-i-just-began-this-book-and-certainly-do">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/35617707-gaurav-andreas"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1537504841i/35617707._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/35617707-gaurav-andreas">Gaurav Andreas</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think we are all certain words that stand out to us. I didn&apos;t notice the word &apos;sweet&apos; a lot perhaps because it immersed with the continuity of the t<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think we are all certain words that stand out to us. I didn't notice the word 'sweet' a lot perhaps because it immersed with the continuity of the text of perfectly. I think you noticed it because the word 'sweet' stands out to you. For me, the word is 'said' which is really unfortunate since it appears in all of the books, probably.<br />If you don't feel enlightened, let's feel dumb together.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
