<div id="review_2062205267" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2062205267" />
    <a title="Khashayar Mohammadi" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32374363-khashayar-mohammadi"><img alt="Khashayar Mohammadi" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1493878334p2/32374363.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2062205267?book_show_action=true">Apr 12, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Khashayar Mohammadi" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Khashayar Mohammadi" href="/user/show/32374363-khashayar-mohammadi">Khashayar Mohammadi</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780316925198" href="/book/show/574933.Brief_Interviews_with_Hideous_Men">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32374363-khashayar-mohammadi?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32374363-khashayar-mohammadi?shelf=north-american-lit">north-american-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/32374363-khashayar-mohammadi?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2062205267" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6060043579730830070">First time I was reading DFW&apos;s fiction and I absolutely loved it. Before this I only knew him as a journalist and essay-writer, but his fiction really floored me. I&apos;m still not a huge fan of his footnotes, but its interesting to see how his stories suddenly branch out into several stories running parallel on both sides of the footnote border. the &quot;Depressed Person&quot; short story immediately became one of my all time favorite stories. One can really feel how he meddles with his page like a TV edito</span>
  <span id="freeText6060043579730830070" style="display:none">First time I was reading DFW's fiction and I absolutely loved it. Before this I only knew him as a journalist and essay-writer, but his fiction really floored me. I'm still not a huge fan of his footnotes, but its interesting to see how his stories suddenly branch out into several stories running parallel on both sides of the footnote border. the "Depressed Person" short story immediately became one of my all time favorite stories. One can really feel how he meddles with his page like a TV editor, making stories emerge from the erasure. the omission in the interviews, the fast forwards and sudden cuts and mistakes that remain uncorrected for a few pages until a new writing tool is introduced to ensure the reader of an underlying meta-narrative; it all showcases DFW's mastery of storytelling. Looking forward to exploring his bibliography furthermore. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6060043579730830070" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


